   1,      1,        1,        1,        2,        2,         2,        1,        1,       1           "Nbs" is the number of BSs, at least 1. 
......Number of BSs must satisfy inequality Nbs(Nbs -1) < W2max (R2/R1)^4, see (II.1) in manual. If you don't need BSs, then take 1 tiny BS, e.g. R1t < R2t/1000, with {ni, Te, u3D} of core. 
	  If you don't need Capsule, then treat it as outer part of Core, i.e. treat R2t as radius of inner part of Core, treat R3t as outer radius of outer part of Core; take same {ni,Te,u3D} in both parts.  
